cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the mu-calculus, a logical framework used in computer science. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with parity games, which are combinatorial representations of games. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses the hierarchy of parity games and their representation as mu-terms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper deals with the classification of parity games into levels of a hierarchy. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the mu-calculus is a formal language used in programming.
